MOTION TO MODIFY SENTENCE - 
The State moves to reopen and vacate the conviction on count 2.  After further investigation, the parties have discovered that count 2 does not reach the felony level.
Court grants motion.
The State files an Amended Information which amends count 2 to misdemeanor theft, contrary to Section 943.20(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge in count 2.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year, consecutive to the prison sentences presently being served, to commence on defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions or probation:
1) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
2) Have no contact with Donald (Scott) Remaker, his residence or any business or real estate he owns;
3) Have no contact with Badgerland Aggregates;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety;
7) Pay court costs;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The Court, on its own motion, amends the length of probation in count 1 to three (3) years which would now be the maximum period.  This probation is also consecutive to the prison sentences presently being served to commence upon defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.
The Court further adds a condition of probation on count 1 of payment of restitution of $4,500.00 to Donald (Scott) Remaker at 9932 County Road JJ, Manitowoc, WI.
State to draft the appropriate order.
Minutes.

